Automatic Execution of Jenkins jobs:
	Build Triggered	: Execute it as per the cron job
	Poll SCM			: Execute as per the changes but we need to define the cron job as well
	Web Hook		: 

Sample Project in GitHub:

In GitHub:
	Settings -> Developer Settings -> Personal Access Token -> Generate New Token -> Give Password
	Token Description => <any-token-name> OR IntegrationWithGitHub
	Select the checkbox for:
		repo
		admin:repo_hook
 		admin:org_hook
	Click on Generate Token
		Copy the token else it will disappear
		8b183c6eb4e2936bdc4a679597c811ac1efedf24

In Jenkins: 
	Click on Credentials
	Click on Jenkins
	Click on “Global Credentials”
	Click on Add Credentials
	kind:
		Username with password:
			Username: IntegrationWithGitHub
			Password: 8b183c6eb4e2936bdc4a679597c811ac1efedf24
			ID: jenkins-secret
		Click on OK
	kind:
		Secret text:
			Secret: 8b183c6eb4e2936bdc4a679597c811ac1efedf24
			ID: jenkins-token

In Jenkins:
	Manage jenkins 
	Configure Systems
	GitHub
	GitHub Server:
		Name: <token-name>	OR IntegrationWithGitHub
		API URL: Default
		Credentials: <select the specified token>
		// Test the connection
		Manage hooks: Select the checkbox
	Click on Save

